aa(lp62
VWe are becoming this global network civilization
p63
aVbecause we are literally building it.
p64
aVAll of the world's defense budgets and military spending taken together
p65
aVtotal just under two trillion dollars per year.
p66
aVMeanwhile, our global infrastructure spending
p67
aVis projected to rise to nine trillion dollars per year
p68
aVwithin the coming decade.
p69
aVAnd, well, it should.
p70
aVWe have been living off an infrastructure stock
p71
aVmeant for a world population of three billion,
p72
aVas our population has crossed seven billion to eight billion
p73
aVand eventually nine billion and more.
p74
aVAs a rule of thumb, we should spend about one trillion dollars
p75
aVon the basic infrastructure needs of every billion people in the world.
p76
aa(lp77
VNot surprisingly, Asia is in the lead.
p78
aVIn 2015, China announced the creation
p79
aVof the Asian Infrastructure Investment Bank,
p80
aVwhich together with a network of other organizations
p81
aVaims to construct a network of iron and silk roads,
p82
aVstretching from Shanghai to Lisbon.
